message.content:
A whiptail is a long and slender lizard with a pointed head and tail. 
They are typically brown or gray in color with darker stripes or spots. 
Their skin is smooth and shiny, with scales that overlap each other. 
Whiptails have four slender legs and are typically around 15-20 inches in length. 
They are found in arid regions across North and South America, often in rocky or desert habitats. 
Whiptails are known for their quick movements and can run at incredible speeds. 
They are mainly insectivores but may occasionally eat small lizards or rodents.
